Japan braces for major typhoon
LOS ANGELES (MarketWatch) -- Japan is bracing for the impact of Typhoon Neoguri, expected to reach Okinawa on Tuesday before heading toward the main island of Kyushu later that day, according to a Kyodo News report Monday. The typhoon may be the strongest for the month of July in decades, and the Japan Meteorological Agency could sissue an emergency warning Monday evening, the report said. Maximum wind speeds for the system are likely to reach more than 194 kilometers per hour (120 miles per hour), Kyodo said.